  "prompt": "I want to change my name in my class 10 CBSE certificate, but I'm currently living in KSA and I'm not an Indian. What should I do?",
  "response": "To change your name on a CBSE Class 10 certificate while living in KSA, follow these steps:\n\n1. Documentation Required:\n- Affidavit stating name change reason\n- Original birth certificate\n- Passport/identity proof\n- School leaving certificate\n- Gazette notification (if applicable)\n\n2. Possible Approaches:\na) Through Indian Embassy in KSA\n- Contact Indian Embassy\n- Submit required documents\n- They will help process name change\n\nb) Directly with CBSE\n- Write to CBSE headquarters\n- Submit all supporting documents\n- Pay prescribed name change fees\n\n3. Online Process:\n- Visit CBSE official website\n- Look for name correction/change section\n- Follow online instructions\n- Upload necessary documents\n\n4. Offline Process:\n- Contact your original school\n- They can help initiate name change process\n- Provide supporting documents\n\n5. Additional Recommendations:\n- Keep all original documents\n- Get documents attested by relevant authorities\n- Maintain clear communication with CBSE\n- Be prepared for potential verification\n\nRecommended: Consult Indian Embassy or CBSE directly for most updated, precise guidance specific to your situation.\n\nWould you like more detailed information about any specific step?",
